Download docker desktop with respect to you os and then login using sudo docker login



1. whomi    

   response: yadav

2.sudo chown -R yadav:yadav /usr/local/lib/node_modules

then create Dockerfile -> nano Dockerfile

3.change docker file like this

FROM node:12-alpine

RUN mkdir -p /home/node/app/node_modules 

WORKDIR /home/node/app

COPY package.json ./home/node/app

RUN npm install 

COPY . /home/node/app

EXPOSE 3000

CMD [ "node", "server.js" ]

4.sudo docker build -t 9962037023:app  . (working sudo docker build -t 9962037023/app  .)

5.sudo docker run 9962037023:app  .

6. pushing image file to docker hub

    sudo docker push 9962037023/app (sudo docker push  9962037023/app:latest)

7. pulling from docker hub and using install 

  sudo docker pull 9962037023/app


8. How to stop docker instance 

     sudo docker stop 0a4582c22c08        --> 0a4582c22c08 this is instance id. u can get it through sudo docker ps


to delete build images  sudo docker system prune -a